article1.headline: Breaking News: Magnitude 5.3 Earthquake Hits Chestin
article1.author: Author: Amy Huang
article1.block1: A magnitude 5.3 earthquake was reported 1 hour ago, 17 miles from Chestin, Calif., according to the U.S. Geological Survey (Source: usgs.gov). They advised that residents should expect aftershocks until later tonight.
article1.block2: This article will be updated with further details to come.

article3.headline: Locals Should Prepare in the Face of Earthquake Warning
article3.author: Author: Richard Becker
article3.block1: The U.S. Geological Survey issued a statement at 3 p.m. today warning residents of Chestin, California to be prepared for a moderate to severe earthquake to hit Chestin County tomorrow. Residents are advised to check for hazards in the home and identify safe places indoors and outdoors.
article3.block2: If an earthquake happens, here are things you can do to protect yourself right away. If you are in a car, pull over, stop, and set your parking brake. If you are in bed, turn face down and cover your head and neck with a pillow. If you are outdoors, stay outdoors away from buildings.
